Greenville.James L. Fleming House: The James L. Fleming House, also known as the Fleming-Winstead House, is a historic home located at 302 S. Greene St. in Greenville, Pitt County, North Carolina. It was built in 1901–1902, and is a 2 1/2-story, frame Queen Anne style dwelling, with design credited to Barber & Klutz who published architectural pattern books.
